# Parallel Agent Delegation

When a task can be split into independent work without merge conflicts, spawn parallel subagents instead of executing everything serially.

Use this checklist before splitting:

1. Confirm each lane has clear boundaries (separate files or modules).
2. Avoid shared bottleneck files in parallel lanes (`package.json`, barrel exports, generated outputs, lockfiles, shared configs).
3. Keep one integration lane for shared-file wiring after isolated lanes finish.

Default behavior:

- Spawn at least one subagent for each safe lane.
- Run independent discovery tasks in parallel when they improve delivery speed.
- If conflict risk is medium/high, do not parallelize that part; keep it in the primary agent lane.

Before finalizing:

- Summarize which lanes were parallelized and why they were safe.
- Call out any deferred serialized integration work explicitly.
